00:21:59.760 --> 00:22:02.730
"Because Babbage never finished
building the analytical engine,

00:22:02.730 --> 00:22:05.390
Ada never got to
see her program run.

00:22:05.390 --> 00:22:07.930
But the influence of
her work lives on.

00:22:07.930 --> 00:22:10.320
More than 100 years
before the invention

00:22:10.320 --> 00:22:13.580
of the modern computer,
Ada had glimpsed the future

00:22:13.580 --> 00:22:17.830
and created a new profession--
computer programming.

00:22:17.830 --> 00:22:20.350
Ada couldn't know that one
day a computer language

00:22:20.350 --> 00:22:23.170
would be named after her-- Ada.

00:22:23.170 --> 00:22:27.900
And one of Ada's uses-- to
guide modern flying machines.

00:22:27.900 --> 00:22:33.350
The girl who needed crutches
ended up flying after all."

00:22:33.350 --> 00:22:35.870
And that's the story of Ada.

